This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring November 20, 2011, as National Child's Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of investing in the health, development, and education of children. It highlights initiatives such as the Healthy, Hunger-Free Kids Act and the Let's Move! campaign aimed at promoting healthy eating habits and reducing childhood obesity. The proclamation also emphasizes the need for a world-class education for all children and calls on citizens to observe the day with appropriate activities and programs.